				"description":"<p></p> <p>Salim Habib University has signed an MoU with The Chemist (Tribe Group of Companies), with the aim of establishing a Quality Pharmaceutical and Clinical Care Training Program in compliance with the national and international standards of pharmacy education proposed by the Accreditation for Pharmacy Education (ACPE) and Pharmacy Council of Pakistan (PCP).</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>The MoU Signing Ceremony was presided over by Prof. Dr. Syed Irfan Hyder, Vice Chancellor SHU and Dr. Zaad Hashmi, Advisory Board Member/Business Partner, The Chemist. Registrar SHU Dr. Muhammad Hussain Habib also graced the ceremony with his presence, along with representatives from the SHU Faculty of Pharmacy, including Dean Prof. Dr. Noor Kamil, Dr. Mudassar Azhar, Associate Professor &amp; Chairman, Dr. Shahnaz Usman, Professor, Dr. Mehmood Shaikh, Associate Professor, Dr. Muhammad Ali Qazi, Assistant Professor, and Ms. Sana Ejaz, Research &amp; Teaching Assistant.</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>Notably present from The Chemist were Mr. Abdul Samad Saadi, Project Admin Manager, Mr. Noman Ahmed, Finance Manager, Mr. Sayed Yasar, Senior Pharmacist, and Ms. Lubna Irshad, In-Charge Pharmacist.</p> <p></p> ","organizer":[{"@type":"Organization","name":"Faculty of Pharmacy"}]}</script></div>
