				"description":"<p></p> <p>The 1st International Conference on Computing &amp; Artificial Intelligence (ICCA-25), organized by the Faculty of Information Technology, Salim Habib University (SHU), at our Fatima Business School, in realization of the vision of the University&#8217;s Honourable Chancellor Dr. Iram Afaq and her mission of revolutionizing education in Pakistan through the incorporation of business technology, science, and artificial intelligence, came to a grand conclusion on Friday, May 16, 2025.</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>The Chief Guest for the Closing Ceremony was Mr. Samiuddin Siddiqui, Secretary to the Governor of Sindh, who was welcomed by Conference Patron and Vice Chancellor SHU Prof. Dr. Syed Irfan Hyder, Chief Operating Officer of The Salim Habib Education Foundation Mr. Muhammad Abbas, Registrar Dr. Muhammad Hussain Habib, Dean Faculty of Information Technology Prof. Dr. Sheeraz Arif, and Chairperson Department of Computer Science Dr. Raazia Sosan. Mr. Samiuddin’s address at the Ceremony inspired all who attended.</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>Guest of Honour Mr. Syed Muhammad Emad Uddin Nizami, CEO Tech Solution Genie and Chairman Hum Hain Shaheen Foundation, also delivered empowering remarks to the audience, as did Vice Chancellor SHU Prof. Dr. Syed Irfan Hyder, officially marking the conclusion of the conference. Reflections were shared by Conference Convener Dr. Raazia Sosan and Conference Secretary Ms. Saadia Karim as well.</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>Thought-provoking keynote sessions based on cutting-edge research were delivered by renowned industry experts and academicians including Dr. Imran Sarwar Bajwa, Professor, Islamia University Bahawalpur, Dr. Uzair Ansari, Director Artificial Intelligence, SUPARCO, and Mr. Qaisar Sarwar, Chief Operating Officer New Horizon Optimum Vision.</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>Another key moment of the Ceremony was the inauguration of the SHU ACM (Association of Computing Machinery) Student Chapter, marking another milestone in SHU’s commitment to excellence in computing education.</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>The second and final day of the conference also featured informative technical sessions, research paper presentations, and panel discussions, attended by a dedicated mix of delegates, scholars, and professionals.&nbsp;</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>In conclusion, ICCA-25 was a phenomenal success that showcased and promoted advancements in Artificial Intelligence, Computer Science, and Cybersecurity, and provided countless opportunities for networking and productive collaborations. We are proud to have hosted such a groundbreaking event and are certain of more landmark events in the future that will also drive innovation and enrich the global landscape of science and research.</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>ICCA25 #ArtificialIntelligence #ComputingConference #Cybersecurity #QuantumComputing #FutureofAI #KeynoteSpeakers #PanelDiscussion #TechLeadership #TechnologicalAdvancement #FatimaBusinessSchool #FBS #SalimHabibUniversity #SHU</p> <p></p> ","organizer":[{"@type":"Organization","name":"Faculty of Information Technology"}]}</script></div>
