				"description":"<p></p> <p>The Department of Business Administration, Faculty of Management Sciences, Salim Habib University, organized a Guest Lecture Series Session for its MBA Weekend Program on Corporate Governance in Pakistan: Challenges, Progress &amp; Future Directions on Sunday, May 17, 2025, as part of the University’s Center of Learning and Teaching (CLT). Approved</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>The session was conducted by Mr. Muhammad Lukman, Chairman, Virtuosoft Pvt. Ltd.</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>ASOPs of Events</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>(These SOPs are needed to be followed by each event societies)</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>document created upon request of VC</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>SOPs of SHU Events</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>Creating a Standard Operating Procedure (SOP) for events organized by student societies ensures consistency, efficiency, and professionalism. Below is a detailed SOP for event planning and execution, tailored to the societies at SHU:</p> <p></p> <p></p> <h1 class='wp-block-heading'>Standard Operating Procedure (SOP) for Event Organization</h1> <p></p> <p></p> <h2 class='wp-block-heading'>&nbsp;1. Pre-Event Planning</h2> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>1.1 Define the Event Objective</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Identify the purpose of the event (e.g., skill development, awareness, entertainment). </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Align the event with the society’s goals and university values. </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>1.2 Form an Event Committee</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Assign roles (e.g., Event Manager, Logistics Head, Marketing Head). </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Ensure clear communication and accountability. </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>1.3 Budget Planning</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Prepare a detailed budget (e.g., venue, decorations, food, marketing). </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Mobilized budget in ratio of 1:2 would be offered by SHU rest would be raised by organizers themselves (i.e., through sponsors)</li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Seek approval from the relevant departments. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Explore sponsorship opportunities if needed. </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>1.4 Venue Booking</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Identify and book a suitable venue well in advance. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Confirm availability, capacity, and technical requirements (e.g., sound system, projector). </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>1.5 Event Timeline</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Create a timeline with deadlines for each task (e.g., marketing, registration, rehearsals). </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Share the timeline with the team and stakeholders. </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h2 class='wp-block-heading'>&nbsp;2. Event Promotion and Registration</h2> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>2.1 Marketing Plan&nbsp;</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Design posters, flyers, and social media posts. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Use platforms like Instagram, Facebook, and WhatsApp for promotion. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Collaborate with the Marketing and Media Society for professional content. </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>2.2 Registration Process&nbsp;</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Set up an online registration form (e.g., Google Forms). </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Specify deadlines and participation criteria (if any). </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Collect necessary details (e.g., name, contact, preferences). </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>2.3 Outreach&nbsp;</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Send reminders via email or social media. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Partner with other societies or departments to widen participation. </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h2 class='wp-block-heading'>&nbsp;3. Logistics and Coordination</h2> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>3.1 Resource Management&nbsp;</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Prepare a checklist of required resources (e.g., chairs, tables, microphones). </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Arrange for transportation and storage of materials. </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>3.2 Technical Setup&nbsp;</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Test all equipment (e.g., sound system, projector) before the event. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Assign a technical team to handle issues during the event. </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>3.3 Decorations and Ambiance&nbsp;</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Plan the layout and decorations based on the event theme. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Ensure the venue is clean and well-organized. </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>3.4 Guest Management&nbsp;</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Invite and confirm attendance of guest speakers, judges, or VIPs. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Arrange for their transportation and accommodation (if needed). </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h2 class='wp-block-heading'>&nbsp;4. Event Execution</h2> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>4.1 Team Briefing&nbsp;</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Conduct a pre-event meeting to assign roles and responsibilities. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Share the event schedule and emergency contacts. </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>4.2 Registration Desk&nbsp;</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Set up a registration counter for checkin. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Provide event kits (e.g., schedules, name tags). </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>4.3 Time Management&nbsp;</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Ensure the event starts and ends on time. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Stick to the schedule for speeches, performances, or activities. </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>4.4 Audience Engagement&nbsp;</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Use interactive elements (e.g., Q&amp;A sessions, polls). </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Ensure the audience is comfortable and informed. </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>4.5 Photography and Videography&nbsp;</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Assign a team to capture high-quality photos and videos. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Pre-planned areas for group photos.</li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Ensure key moments (e.g., speeches, performances) are documented. </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h2 class='wp-block-heading'>&nbsp;5. Post Event Activities</h2> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>5.1 Feedback Collection&nbsp;</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Distribute feedback forms or conduct online surveys. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Gather suggestions for improvement. </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>5.2 Thank You Notes&nbsp;</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Send thankyou emails or messages to participants, guests, and sponsors. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Acknowledge the efforts of the organizing team. </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>5.3 Financial Reconciliation&nbsp;</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Review expenses and compare them with the budget. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Submit a financial report to the relevant department (i.e., Student Affairs or Audit). </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>5.4 Event Report&nbsp;</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Prepare a detailed report summarizing the event (e.g., objectives, outcomes, challenges). </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Include photos, videos, and feedback highlights. </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h3 class='wp-block-heading'>5.5 Social Media Highlights&nbsp;</h3> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li>Share event highlights on social media platforms. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li>Tag participants, sponsors, and collaborators. </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h1 class='wp-block-heading'>&nbsp;Society Specific Event Ideas</h1> <p></p> <p></p> <p>Here are some event ideas tailored to each society:</p> <p></p> <p></p> <h2 class='wp-block-heading'>&nbsp;1. Marketing and Media Society&nbsp;</h2> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li><strong>Workshop</strong>: Social Media Marketing and Branding. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li><strong>Event</strong>: Creative Ad Making Competition. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li><strong>Collaboration</strong>: Promote university wide events through posters and videos. </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h2 class='wp-block-heading'>&nbsp;2. Arts and Literature Society&nbsp;</h2> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li><strong>Event</strong>: Poetry Slam or Open Mic Night. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li><strong>Workshop</strong>: Creative Writing and Storytelling. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li><strong>Exhibition</strong>: Art and Photography Showcase. </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h2 class='wp-block-heading'>&nbsp;3. Public Speaking Society&nbsp;</h2> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li><strong>Event</strong>: Debate Competition on Current Topics. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li><strong>Workshop</strong>: Overcoming Stage Fear and Effective Communication. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li><strong>Activity</strong>: Mock Parliament or Model United Nations (MUN). </li> <p></ul> <p></p> <p></p> <h2 class='wp-block-heading'>&nbsp;4. Character Building Society&nbsp;</h2> <p></p> <p></p> <ul class='wp-block-list'></p> <li><strong>Workshop</strong>: Leadership and Team Building. </li> <p></p> <p></p> <li><strong>Event</strong>: Community Service Day (e.g., cleanliness