				"description":"<p></p> <p>Salim Habib University (SHU) has inked an MoU with the Aga Khan University (AKU). The aim of the MoU is to provide SHU Biomedical Engineering students with hands-on training and research opportunities at AKU&#8217;s Centre for Innovation in Medical Education (CIME) through internships, field visits, seminars, and collaborative technical events.&nbsp;</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>The initiation of this incredible partnership would not have been possible without the dedicated efforts of Engr. Gul Munir, Senior Lecturer, Faculty of Engineering, SHU.</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>The MoU Signing Ceremony was presided over by Prof. Dr. Syed Irfan Hyder, Vice Chancellor SHU, and Dr. Faisal Ismail, Regional Director, AKU-CIME. Registrar SHU Dr. Muhammad Hussain Habib and Mr. Saleem Shahabuddin, Manager Simulation Technology, AKU-CIME, also graced the ceremony with their presence as did Dr. Anjum Halai, Professor &amp; Vice Provost, AKU, and Mr. Ghulam Nabie, Advisor, AKU-CIME.</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>Notably present from SHU were Engr. Hassan Ali, Senior Lecturer, Department of Biomedical Engineering, and Ms. Pariwash Khan, Deputy Registrar</p> <p></p> "}</script></div>
